5 Agent Mutation Testing
Mutation testing assesses test suite quality by measuring its ability to detect injected faults. For traditional software, mutants are syntactic source code modifications. For AI agents, the “source” comprises prompts, tool configurations, models, and context—requiring entirely new mutation operators. This section defines four classes of agent-specific mutation operators, formalizes the mutation score under stochastic semantics, and proves a mutation adequacy theorem.
