The cost savings are remarkably consistent: 77–78% across all three models and all three scenarios (Table 7). Mistral-Large-3, the most expensive model at $0.338 per regression check, saves $0.262 per check with SPRT alone. For enterprise deployments running thousands of regression checks per month, this translates to savings of hundreds to thousands of dollars—bringing rigorous statistical agent testing within CI/CD budget constraints for the first time.
